product_name: Charlotte TilburyUnreal Lip + Cheek Glow Blush Stick
summary: SummaryCharlotte Tilbury's Unreal Lip + Cheek Glow Blush Stick is an ultra-hydrating, luminous blush with buildable + blendable color that lasts for up to 8 hours* on cheeks and lips.
details: DetailsFeaturesCharlotte's Unreal Blush is supercharged with skin-loving ingredients that hydrate and plump while delivering long-lasting color for a buttery smooth application.This easy-to-use formula features micro-fine pearlescent pigments for a glazed-sheen, luminous pop of color on cheeks and lips.Research ResultsInstantly moisturizes*Locks in hydration for up to 24 hours*Helps strengthen the skin barrier*Skin looks +89% smoother**Color lasts for up to 8 hours on cheeks & lips**tested on 33 people**tested on 33 people after one applicationKey IngredientsCollageener: Firms and smoothes skinMulti-Molecular Weight Hyaluronic Acid: Intensely moisturizes and hydrates for up to 24 hoursColour Light Mapping Mesh Tech: Pearlescent pigments diffuse light for a dream-sheen luminous finishItem 2641371How To UseBuild and blend across cheeks and/or lips with your finger or brush for an unreal pop of color.Tilbury tip: Apply across the bridge of your nose to mimic a natural sun-kissed glow!IngredientsCherry Glow : C15-19 Alkane, Octyldodecanol, Tridecyl Trimellitate, Mica, Polyethylene, Polybutene, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Dimer Dilinoleyl Dimer Dilinoleate, Dicalcium Phosphate, Sucrose Tetrastearate Triacetate, Raphanus Sativus (Radish) Seed Extract, Cera Microcristallina/Microcrystalline Wax/Cire Microcristalline, Silica, Silica Silylate, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Tocopheryl Acetate, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Propylene Carbonate, Ricinus Communis (Castor) Seed Oil, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Hydrolyzed Sodium Hyaluronate, Lupinus Albus Seed Extract, Sodium Hyaluronate, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Tocopherol, Rosemarinus Officinalis (Rosemary) Leaf Oil. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77499), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Build and blend across cheeks and/or lips with your finger or brush for an unreal pop of color.Tilbury tip: Apply across the bridge of your nose to mimic a natural sun-kissed glow!

reviews.headline: Glowy with Shine!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This blush is so gorgeous and glowy! It's so creamy and easy to blend. It is subtle and perfect for a natural day. You do have to layer twice if you want more color to come through. Over all, it does what it claims to do!

reviews.headline: Beautiful...
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush stick is so pretty! The color looks super pigmented and bold, but has a very natural look to it on your face or lips. It's so soft as it glides on and easily blends. I like that it has skin-loving ingredients in it that helps hydrate. 

I noticed it lasted, but not as long as claimed ( for me, at least ). Also, the packaging, while pretty, felt cheap-ish and the stick kept falling out from the tube. Easy to put back in, but super annoying.

reviews.headline: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I
reviews.comments: I love anything Charlotte tilbury. The perfect line for a glowy and double taking look! You can build it up and itll still be effortlessly blended nicely. I always recommend her line to anyone. Over all 10 out of 10 recommend

reviews.headline: Good
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It's very natural! But it's also very buildable. I love the color and the way it feels, my only problem was that it arrived broken but other than that I love!

reviews.headline: Perfect blush stick!
reviews.comments: I'm in love with the Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick! It gives a natural, healthy glow, has a light pleasant scent, and comes in beautiful, travel-friendly packaging. The texture is smooth and creamy, easy to blend, and keeps my face looking fresh all day.

reviews.headline: Blush your face with one swipe!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange of my honest review] I'm not pink blush person but this Rosy Glow is beautiful! It has a smooth and creamy texture! It's very easy to apply with your fingers. You only need one swipe of the blush though, the pigment is high. I would love to try another color for sure. One down side is that the tube came out of the bottom as soon as I opened it.

reviews.headline: I love the color
reviews.comments: I am obsessed with the formula and how easy it is to use! I love the creamyness that blends so easily.

reviews.headline: Amazing only if doing minimal coverage
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Overall I thought this was okay. The stick unfortunately pulled my foundation up when I used it which was a bother. When I wore it without foundation it was pretty nice, just not the most noticeable.

reviews.headline: Absolutely yes
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Glowy beautiful blush. The color is so perfect for summer. I love the texture because it doesn't create a greasy effect but more like healthy natural flash

reviews.headline: Radiant Cheeks
reviews.comments: Charlotte Tilbury's Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick in Pinky Glow is a dream for fresh, radiant cheeks. The creamy stick glides on effortlessly, blends like silk, and leaves a natural pink flush that looks like it comes from within. It's buildable, long-lasting, and never glitteryâ€”just that perfect healthy glow. A little goes a long way, making it worth the splurge.

reviews.headline: I would buy again
reviews.comments: This blush is very hydrating and smoothing. It's very easy to apply to your cheeks and rub it in. It's almost like a balm and creates a soft glow. It lasts until you wash it off and it's easy. Definitely recommend if you like pink blushes!

reviews.headline: Blendable with great staying power
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my *always* honest review] 

I've tried creams and powders, but the Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick (in Rosy Glow) was new to me. It's basically a big twist-up tube, and you dot it on your cheeks and blend. I tried it with a beauty blender and just my fingers, but found using a short bristled brush worked best. 

The color itself has decent pigment (so you don't need much) but it's also sheer enough that it's super blendable, and it has a nice subtle shimmer. It's NOT mirror ball glittery, which I've found is sometimes the case with Tilbury products. It also has decent staying power â€” on me it lasted all day with no touchups.

reviews.headline: Rosy Glow on cheeks & lips
reviews.comments: Trying Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush in Rosy Glow and honestlyâ€¦ it's so soft and creamy ðŸ˜Œ. Blends like a dream, gives that natural flush without looking overdone, and I can even swipe a bit on my lips. Simple, fresh, glowy â€” love it.

reviews.headline: So pretty and so easy to use!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I 've been trying out the new Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick and I really like how easy it is to use. The texture is creamy, blends super smoothly, and gives my cheeks that natural, glowy flush without looking heavy. I also like that it feels hydrating, so my skin doesn't look dry or patchy. The stick format makes it quick for me to swipe on and go, perfect for busy mornings. It lasts well through the day and keeps that healthy glow. Definitely a blush I'd reach for when I want something effortless but still radiant.

reviews.headline: So pretty!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love the formula and packaging for this blush.  Just a little color on the cheeks is all you need. The blush is buildable and bendable. Highly recommended.

reviews.headline: A must have
reviews.comments: This is so cool and amazing perfect for everyday. The texture is very lightweight and glides onto the skin so beautifully

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love this blush! It's easy to apply and easy to blend out. The pigmentation is amazing and you don't need a lot so it will last a while too! The packaging is adorable too

reviews.headline: Love!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Summer glow just got a major upgrade I've been loving the Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush Stick in Pinky Glow The formula melts right into my skin and gives that effortless flush that actually lasts through the day. Super easy to swipe on and blendâ€”plus it doubles up beautifully on the lips for that fresh, put-together look without even trying Perfect for those "no-makeup makeup" days or when you want a soft radiant pop.

reviews.headline: natural glow that's easy to apply
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I tried the Charlotte Tilbury Blush and I love how easy it is to apply. The creamy stick blends effortlessly, doesn't dry my skin, and gives a fresh, natural-looking color. It feels lightweight and leaves a nice healthy glow without looking shiny

reviews.headline: A must have
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really love it the pigmentation it's amazing ! The texture the scent the packaging it's a must have !! It's blends so well and it last for a long time !!!

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick is a game-changer in the world of blush products.
Its sleek, portable design makes it perfect for on-the-go touch-ups.
The stick format allows for precise application and easy blending.
The texture is incredibly creamy, gliding effortlessly onto the skin.
It feels lightweight and comfortable, almost as if you're not wearing anything at all.
The pigmentation is buildable, giving you control over the intensity of the color.
In its natural state, the shade offers a beautiful, healthy-looking glow.
The color payoff is natural yet luminous, mimicking the effect of a post-workout flush.
The formula contains nourishing ingredients that add to the skin's overall health.
It blends seamlessly with other makeup products or can be worn alone for a fresh look.
The shade "Healthy Glow" is versatile; flattering for many skin tones.
The finish is radiant but not overly shiny, striking a perfect balance.
I've noticed that it lasts quite well throughout the day, maintaining its glow.
The mobility of the stick formula allows for quick makeup routines.
Cleanup is easy, and there's no stubborn staining left behind.
The packaging feels luxe, with a weighty, high-quality feel.
It's a great option for busy mornings when you need a quick pop of color.
The scent is subtle and pleasant, typical of Charlotte Tilbury's luxurious line.
It pairs beautifully with powder or liquid foundations, enhancing the overall look.
The stick is less messy than traditional blush powders, reducing fallout.
In comparison to other cream blushes, it offers a more natural, skin-like finish.
The product is quite durable, maintaining its vibrancy from morning to night.
Overall, the Charlotte Tilbury Unreal Blush Healthy Glow Stick is a fantastic addition to any makeup collection.
It's perfect for those seeking a quick, natural glow with minimal fuss.
